messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /cms/file

All HTTP methods acceptable?
- No

Allowed methods (based on the code):
- HEAD: No
- POST: Yes
- OPTIONS: No
- TRACE: No
- GET: No
- PUT: No
- DELETE: No
- PATCH: No

Explanation:
- The app registers the CMS blueprint with url_prefix "/cms" in app/__init__.py (app.register_blueprint(create_cms(), url_prefix="/cms")).
- Inside app/api/cms/__init__.py the file blueprint is registered on the CMS blueprint with url_prefix "/file" (cms.register_blueprint(file_api, url_prefix="/file")). Blueprint prefixes are concatenated, producing the base path "/cms/file".
- In app/api/cms/file.py the route is declared as @file_api.route("", methods=["POST"]). The empty route string attaches to the blueprint prefix, giving the final path "/cms/file".
- The route explicitly lists methods=["POST"], so only POST is allowed by the code. Other methods (HEAD, GET, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, PATCH) are not declared acceptable per the source; the result reflects only what the code specifies, not framework runtime behaviors (e.g., implicit OPTIONS/HEAD handling).
